2. Create a vector, array or list called `sums` which will store the sum of all non-empty continuous subarrays;
3. Iterate through `nums`, and for each position `i`, create another loop from `i` to `n - 1`, adding the elements to create the sum of the current subarray and appending or inserting it into `sums`.
4. Sort `sums` in non-decreasing order using `sort()` or `Arrays.sort()`. For Python and Javascript, you might need to implement a compare function;
5. Iterate through `sums` from index `left - 1` to `right - 1`, accumulating the desired subarray sums in variable `result`. Make sure to apply the modulo operation to the result in each addition;
6. Return the result.

